The second season of Hataraku Maou-sama! MgRonald’s best demon lord worker is back, climbing the corporate ladder to become ruler of Earth. But Maou’s plans of domination might need to be put on hold when a small girl claims to be his and Emi’s child! (Source: Crunchyroll)

When an online game turns real, trapping its players in its virtual space, the strongest of them, Shin, rises up to put a stop to the madness. But just moments after defeating the game’s final boss, Origin, and freeing everyone, Shin is transported 500 years into the future of the in-game world. Armed with unrivaled strength, the young swordsman embarks on a legendary journey.
(Source: Crunchyroll)
Kaguya-sama wa Kokurasetai: Tensaitachi no Renai Zunousen

Kaguya and Miyuki have a mindgame on their way to the Student Council room. Note: One shot published in Weekly Young Jump to promote the (then new) series. It was included in the fanbook, but not in any volumes.

A quirky yuri comedy about the chaotic daily life of high school girls!
Yokoe and Sugiura have been together forever, and they’ve mastered the art of making trouble when life’s a bore. High school might be a drag, but these girls in love know just how to inject a little chaos and comedy into their sloppy school life.
(Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)
